'''Queen Noor Civil Aviation Technical College''' (Acronym: QNAC or QNCATC; [[Arabic language|Arabic]]:  الملكة نور الفنية للطيران المدني كلية ) is a private engineering college located in [[Aqaba]], [[Jordan]].<ref name=UD>{{cite web|title=Queen Noor Civil Aviation Technical College|url=http://www.university-directory.eu/Jordan/Queen-Noor-Civil-Aviation-Technical-College.html|publisher=University directory|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref><ref name=Zawya>{{cite web|title=Queen Noor Civil Aviation Technical College|url=https://www.zawya.com/company/profile/1000353/Queen_Noor_Civil_Aviation_Technical_College/|publisher=Zawya|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref> This college was established in 1973 with support of [[International Civil Aviation Organization|ICAO]].<ref name=ClassBase>{{cite web|title=Queen Noor Civil Aviation Technical College|url=http://www.classbase.com/Countries/Jordan/Universities/Queen-Noor-Civil-Aviation-Technical-College-25530|publisher=ClassBase|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref> In 1990 the college became one of the first members of the ICAO TRAINAIR Program.<ref name="About the college">{{cite web|title=About the college|url=http://www.qnac.edu.jo/about-us|publisher=QNAC|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref>

