'''The Fullbridge Program''' is a learning curriculum held by [[educational technology]] company Fullbridge, Inc. which teaches basic business techniques.<ref name=denver>{{cite web| url=http://www.denverpost.com/2013/06/23/fullbridge-program-gives-colorado-undergrads-crash-course-in-business/| publisher=The Denver Post| title=Fullbridge Program gives Colorado undergrads crash course in business| author=Adrian D. Garcia| date=June 23, 2013| access-date=December 5, 2017}}</ref>
==History== Fullbridge Inc. was founding by former [[Random house]] chairman Peter Olson and his wife, [[iVillage]] founder [[Candice Carpenter Olson]], in 2010.<ref name=ed>{{cite web| url=https://www.edsurge.com/news/fullbridge-5-5-million| publisher=EdSurge| title=Fullbridge $5.5 Million| date=May 30, 2012| access-date=December 5, 2017}}</ref><ref name=denver/>
In January 2012, Fullbridge launched a pilot program aimed at college students and recent graduates, and subsequently focused on larger programs that summer. Then Fullbridge established a suite of vertical business-to-business programs for law firms, consulting firms, financial firms, service organizations, universities, and corporations.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} In September 2012, Fullbridge partnered with Andrews Kurth to expand the law firm's attorney professional development program. Andrews Kurth was the third law firm in the United States to partner with Fullbridge.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.andrewskurth.com/news-371.html| publisher=Andrews Kurth| title=Andrews Kurth Collaborates with The Fullbridge Program to Help Prepare New Associates for the Practice of Law| date=September 6, 2012| access-date=December 5, 2017}}</ref>
Fullbridge has worked in the [[Kingdom of Saudi Arabia]] helping young women prepare for new vocational opportunities and offered a four-week Business Fundamentals Program at [[Prince Sultan University]].{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}
Fullbridge started out in [[Harvard Square|Harvard Square, Cambridge, MA]], and later moved to [[Downtown Crossing, Boston, Massachusetts|Downtown Boston, MA]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ed Tech Company Fullbridge Looks to Expand With $5M in New Funding|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2014/10/14/ed-tech-company-fullbridge-looks-to-expand-with-5m-in-new-funding/|website=Wall Street Journal}}</ref>
In 2012, Fullbridge received $5.5 million in funding from GSV Capital Corp., Tomorrow Ventures, and Harris Preston.<ref name=ed/>
In summer 2013, The Fullbridge Program was presented at Red Rocks Community College in Arvada, Colorado.<ref name=denver/>
